    "body": "## Pull request overview\n\nThis PR clarifies that wildcard groups (`pathGroupings`) in Paths (including exclusions) are a paid “Advanced paths” feature, across the UI and the AI/MCP guidance surfaces, so free-plan users get an explicit upgrade explanation instead of a generic empty/disabled state.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Update Paths exclusions tooltip copy to mention wildcard groups require a paid plan.\n- Add a paid-plan-specific hover tooltip for the gated empty “Wildcards” taxonomic category, plus a small helper + Jest coverage.\n- Teach PostHog AI tool prompt and MCP/skill references that `pathGroupings` (wildcard groups) are paid-only and should not prompt workarounds for free users.\n\n### Reviewed changes\n\nCopilot reviewed 6 out of 6 changed files in this pull request and generated 1 comment.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>\n\n| File | Description |\r\n| ---- | ----------- |\r\n| services/mcp/definitions/prompts/query-paths.md | Adds paid-plan note for `pathGroupings` in the MCP Paths prompt and reminders. |\r\n| products/posthog_ai/skills/querying-posthog-data/references/example-paths.md.j2 | Adds paid-plan guidance note for wildcard groups in the querying skill reference. |\r\n| frontend/src/queries/nodes/InsightViz/EditorFilters.tsx | Updates exclusions tooltip wording to mention wildcard groups require a paid plan. |\r\n| frontend/src/lib/components/TaxonomicFilter/InfiniteSelectResults.tsx | Adds paygate-specific disabled reason and Tooltip behavior for gated Wildcards category. |\r\n| frontend/src/lib/components/TaxonomicFilter/InfiniteSelectResults.test.tsx | Adds parameterized unit tests for the new disabled-reason helper. |\r\n| ee/hogai/tools/create_insight.py | Updates the tool prompt to avoid pretending Paths edits are supported and to explain the paid gate for wildcard groups. |\n</details>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n---\n\n💡 <a href=\"/PostHog/posthog/new/master?filename=.github/instructions/*.instructions.md\" class=\"Link--inTextBlock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Add Copilot custom instructions</a> for smarter, more guided reviews. <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/customizing-copilot/adding-repository-custom-instructions-for-github-copilot\" class=\"Link--inTextBlock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Learn how to get started</a>.",
