    "author": "webjunkie",
    "state": "APPROVED",
    "submitted_at": "2026-06-24T19:34:59+00:00",
    "body": "Independently verified on a real PR run (28113767618): the experiments product shards log `No test durations found` and flat-split by count (811/810 equal selected), producing real pytest times of 24:52 vs 12:22 — genuine execution imbalance, not step-wall/overhead noise. The repo-root `.test_durations` is already restored in the product job and contains matching `products/experiments/…` keys (no colliding bare `backend/` keys), so pointing `--durations-path` at it binds correctly. This PR's own run shows the shards balancing (11:19 vs 10:07). Correct diagnosis, minimal fix, helps every multi-shard product on PRs. LGTM.\n\nMinor: the win scales with how uneven a branch's tests are (~6 min off the long pole on heavy branches); the literal '12-13 min each' is branch-dependent, not guaranteed.",
    "commit_id": "6b7ceb2a2dc8045c630eaf1197d88b1dc8799504",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/PostHog/posthog/pull/65877#pullrequestreview-4565310852"
